		  <td class="forum_boardrow1" style="border-width: 0px 1px 1px 1px;" valign="top"><div id="message29025721">Well, that was a pretty sweet short. It told a rather nice story about growing up and the different phases of life. Particularly liked the part where they showed the girl becoming more and more aloof from her family. The animation as usual was amazing but that's to be expected from a shinkai work, I guess. The ending song was really good too. The dialogue as said is really adorable, particularly the interactions between the daughter and the father at the dinner table bringing up all sorts of nostalgic scenes.</div><div class="postActions"></div><div class="sig">[25/04/14 4:04:39 PM] Skitzo: doujins have deep psychological undertones about the sexual intrigue of human behavior</div></td>
