		  <td class="forum_boardrow1" style="border-width: 0px 1px 1px 1px;" valign="top"><div id="message29043393"><!--quote--><div class="quotetext"><strong>Aryaragi said:</strong><!--quotesaid--><br>The animation as usual was amazing but that's to be expected from a shinkai work, I guess.<!--quote--></div><br />
One thing I can say of all of Shinkai's work is that you can take any individual frame and have something beautiful that you could frame and put on your wall.  But animation refers to the <em>kinetic</em> aspect of the visuals--and Shinkai's work delivers very little on that front.  Beautiful art, lackluster animation.<br />
<br />
I don't see this as a problem, necessarily.  There are lots of places that linger on a still frame, and if the intent is to allow the viewer to look at beautifully drawn frames, then reproducing them seems like an effective means of achieving that.  But again, it's hard to praise the animation when the best thing that can be said about the animation is that there isn't much of it.</div><div class="postActions"></div></td>
		</tr></table></div><div class="forum_boardrowspacer">&nbsp;</div>
