		  <td class="forum_boardrow1" style="border-width: 0px 1px 1px 1px;" valign="top"><div id="message29063507">This wasn't purely an advertisement for the company that sponsored the animation; there's no blatant advertisement during the short - which saves this project, somehow.... <br />
<br />
We again, see how a human being grows and tries to live a common life, studying, working and living alone - all of this will won't have any emotional depth on the viewer that doesn't relate at all with the experiences that the character is going through, and this short relies a lot on that. Good thing the production values were high (this is very important, gives the immersion needed due to its short length) and I guess the conclusion was okay, I didn't expected much out of it.</div><div style="margin-top: 8px;"><em>Modified by mosaic, 03-05-14, 9:30 PM</em></div><div class="postActions"></div></td>
